message.msgid: This feature can be used only if wireless is enabled.
message.msgstr: This feature can be used only if wireless is enabled.

Wi-Fi Protected Setup (WPS) makes it easy for home users who know little of wireless security to establish a secure wireless home network, as well as to add new devices to an existing network without entering long passphrases or configuring complicated settings. Simply enter a PIN code or press the software PBC button or hardware WPS button (if any) and a secure wireless connection is established. The WPS can be used only when security mode: None, WPA2-PSK or Mixed WPA/WPA2-PSK and cipher type: AES or TKIP&AES are selected.
Network mode will switch to 11b/g mixed automatically if WEP or TKIP is selected;
Network Mode will switch to 11b/g/n mixed automatically if AES or TKIP&AES is selected.
